    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STOPMASTER WEDGE TYPE BRAKE - TROUBLESHOOT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x0401303" svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="7">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOT</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>When the brakes are equipped with spring brake units, cage the power springs before starting any
                    troubleshooting or removal of wheels and drums
                </para>
                <para>All spring brake units have a warning imprinted on either a metal tag or on the unit's housing
                    stating that the spring is pre-loaded. This unit should be replaced entirely if its functionality is
                    in question. Do not disassemble.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <table id="t0401301" tblwidth="full-page">
            <title>Troubleshooting Table</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="2.5in"/>
                <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="2.5in"/>
                <colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="2.5in" colsep="1"/>
                <thead valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>CONDITION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>POSSIBLE CAUSE</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>REMEDY</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry morerows="5">
                            <para>AUTOMATIC ADJUSTERS NOT WORKING</para>
                            <graphic id="g0401345" filename="../figg04/G0401345.webp" type="webp"/>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1. Detent spring damaged or broken.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Bolt threads tight in actuator.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove, clean or replace.Adjusting bolt must not extend beyond bottom of actuator and
                                actuator must seat on abutment shoulder of plunger.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Adjusting plunger improperly installed.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Correct installation. Arrow stamped on shoe should point away from adjusting plunger
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Seal improperly installed</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Example: seal jammed into threads, causing binding. Remove and replace.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5. Damaged pawl and anchor teeth due to lack of lubrication.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Lubricate and install new pawl assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>6. Adjusting pawl spring collapsed or missing.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Check spring tension. Tension should be 7-1/2 lbs. (3.4 kg) compressed to 9/16" (14.29
                                mm). Condition questionable; replace.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry morerows="3">
                            <para>SPRING BRAKE NOT HOLDING</para>
                            <graphic id="g0401346" filename="../figg04/G0401346.webp" type="webp"/>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1. Power spring not fully uncaged or broken.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Be sure brake unit is uncaged. If spring is broken, replace spring brake assembly.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Air not releasing brake</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Air lines plugged; repair or replace. Faulty spring brake control valve at instrument
                                panel; repair or replace.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Caging bolt damaged.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace spring brake unit.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Brakes not adjusted properly.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Adjust brakes.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry morerows="9">
                            <para>BRAKES DRAGGING</para>
                            <graphic id="g0401347" filename="../figg04/G0401347.webp" type="webp"/>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1. Spring brake power spring not fully releasing.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Low spring hold off pressure. Replace spring brake assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Improper connection of service and spring brake air lines.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Correct installation.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Shoe return spring not fully returning shoes.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace return springs.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Leaking air lines or seals.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Repair or replace</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5. Trapped air behind spring brake unit power piston in service brake.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Repair or replace.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>6. Loose wheel bearings.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Adjust wheel bearings.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>7. Wedge shaft out of push rod socket.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Improper assembly; wedge guide missing or broken. Correct or replace.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>8. Plungers tight or sticking</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Caused by corrosion due to seal failure or improper lubrication. Replace seal, clean
                                and lubricate.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>9. Broken wedge return spring or cotter pin.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Repair or replace.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>10. Grease or dirt on lining due to bad seals or lack of dust shields.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace wheel seals. Correct dust shield installation.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry morerows="4">
                            <para>BRAKES GRABBING</para>
                            <graphic id="g0401348" filename="../figg04/G0401348.webp" type="webp"/>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1. Low air pressure to service brakes.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check pressure. Delivery pressure should be approximately the same as chassis pressure
                                (refer to AIR SYSTEM section of manual).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Grease or dirt on lining due to bad wheel seals.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace wheel seals and clean lining. Use denatured alcohol to clean lining. If lining
                                cannot be cleaned to satisfaction, replace lining.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Improper lining.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Install proper lining. Use only International approved material.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Misaligned wedge and plunger parts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove, clean and replace worn components.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5. Binding of brake shoes.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Improper assembly, worn shoes or return springs. Check installation and replace all
                                worn or damaged parts.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry morerows="2">
                            <para>BRAKES FROZEN OR LOCKED</para>
                            <graphic id="g0401349" filename="../figg04/G0401349.webp" type="webp"/>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1. Spring brake units not releasing.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace spring brake unit.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Air not releasing from service brakes.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Correct faulty condition in air system.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Seized plungers.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove, clean and lubricate. Replace any faulty parts. Replace seals</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry morerows="9">
                            <para>UNEVEN LINING WEAR</para>
                            <graphic id="g0401350" filename="../figg04/G0401350.webp" type="webp"/>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1. Wedge shaft out of push-rod socket.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Correct assembly. Replace wedge guide if missing or broken.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Brake shoes installed backwards.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Correct installation of shoes.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Weak brake shoe return spring.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace springs.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Wedge rollers not engaged with plunger slots.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Inspect and correct installation.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5. Brake lining material mixed.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Do not mix brake material. Use only International approved material.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>6. Grease or dirt on lining.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace wheel seals and use denatured alcohol to clean lining. If lining cannot be
                                cleaned to satisfaction, replace lining.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>7. Shoe hold down clips not retaining shoes against support pads.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace support pads.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>8. Brake drums deflected or bell-mouthed.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Defective brake drum; replace drum.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>9. Automatic adjuster not functioning properly.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove, clean and replace any defective parts.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>10. Roller out of cage.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Correct installation of rollers.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry morerows="7">
                            <para>INSUFFICIENT BRAKE TORQUE</para>
                            <graphic id="g0401351" filename="../figg04/G0401351.webp" type="webp"/>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1. Automatic adjusters not functioning.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove, clean, lubricate and replace seals.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Lining worn out.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace lining.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Low friction lining used.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Use only International approved brake material.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Plungers frozen in spider.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove, clean, lubricate and replace any faulty parts.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5. Grease on lining</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace wheel seals and use denatured alcohol to clean lining. If lining cannot be
                                cleaned to satisfaction replace lining.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>6. Ruptured air chamber diaphragm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace diaphragm.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>7. Spring brake chamber not fully threaded into housing.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Properly install spring brake chamber.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>8. Air system leaks.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Correct air leaks</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
